parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of motorized seat belts can lead to accidents, injuries, or entrapment, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract
sticks to the floor

or gets jammed; the belt does not stay in the correct position; the belt retracts without warning while the car is in motion; the belt catches on the sunvisor and breaks it; the belt fails to release or move forward when the vehicle is shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inoperative seat belt retractors can cause the seat belt to fail to function properly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor fails to work
the belt does not retract
the belt gets stuck
or the belt does not stay in the correct position.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Issues with Motorized Seat Belts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly address recall issues with motorized seat belts can lead to ongoing safety risks, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Recall work was not performed correctly
wrong parts were installed
or parts were not received; the recall did not resolve the issue
and the motorized seat belt still malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the door to fly open while driving, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, and may also prevent the door from being opened from the inside or outside, trapping occupants.
symptoms: The door cannot be opened from the inside or outside
the door latch fails
the door flies open while driving
the door unlatches when the window is lowered
the door is stuck shut.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the front axle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may become unstable or even break apart while driving.
symptoms: The front axle rusts completely
the front axle breaks apart while driving
unusual noises or vibrations from the front axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Jumping Out of Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jumping out of gear can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may suddenly accelerate or decelerate without warning.
symptoms: The transmission jumps out of gear
the transmission slips or hesitates
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause loss of power, stalling, or complete loss of vehicle operation, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: The transmission fails
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The speedometer cable failure can cause inaccurate or no speed readings, which can lead to speeding or other safety issues.
symptoms: The speedometer cable severs
the speedometer reading is inaccurate or not working.
